<module>
    <h>gille</h>
    <p><g>gille</g>
        <en>a boy</en> is a masculine <a href="?xx=nouns/simple_common_nouns">simple common
        noun</a>.</p>

    <p>Examples of <g>gille</g> as the subject of the predicative verb <a href="?gd=bi"
            ><g>bi</g></a> – <ul>
            <li>pre-specified – <ul>
                    <li>definite article – <g>an gille</g>
                        <en>the boy</en> – <ul>
                            <li>unmodified – <xl>
                                    <li>
                                        <gd>Tha an gille mór.</gd>
                                        <tr>The boy is big.</tr>
                                        <ref text="617">td. 15</ref>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <gd>Cha robh an gille aig an dorus.</gd>
                                        <tr>The boy was not at the door.</tr>
                                        <ref text="617">td. 15</ref>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <gd>A bheil an gille a’ cluich? Tha,</gd>
                                        <tr>Is the boy playing? Yes, he is.</tr>
                                        <ref text="617">td. 15</ref>
                                    </li>
                                </xl>
                            </li>
                            <li>attributive adjective – <xl>
                                    <li>
                                        <gd>Càit a bheil an gille beag an diugh?</gd>
                                        <tr>Where is the little boy today?</tr>
                                        <ref text="617">td. 14</ref>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <gd>A bheil an gille beag anns an sgoil? Chan eil.</gd>
                                        <tr>Is the little boy in the school? No, he isn’t.</tr>
                                        <ref text="617">td. 14 [227]</ref>
                                    </li>
                                </xl>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </p>

    <p>Examples of <g>gille</g> as the subject of a demonstrative pronoun used as a copular verb – <ul>
            <li>pre-specified – <ul>
                    <li>definite article – <ul>
                            <li>unmodified – <xl>
                                    <li>
                                        <gd>Seo an gille.</gd>
                                        <tr>This is the boy.</tr>
                                        <ref text="617">td. 15</ref>
                                    </li>
                                </xl>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </p>

    <p>Examples of <g>gille</g> as the complement of the preposition <a href="?gd=air"
            ><g>air</g></a>
        <en>on</en> – <ul>
            <li>pre-specified – <ul>
                    <li>definite article – <g>air a’ ghille</g>
                        <en>on the boy</en> – <ul>
                            <li>demonstrative – <xl>
                                    <li>
                                        <gd>Dé tha ceàrr air a’ ghille seo? Tha a cheann goirt.</gd>
                                        <tr>What is wrong with this boy? His head is sore.</tr>
                                        <ref text="617">td. 20</ref>
                                    </li>
                                </xl>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </p>

</module>
